results.name: Distinct values of A218787 in the order of appearance.
comment: a(n) = A014486-index for the n-th tendril of the infinite beanstalk (A179016), which has not been encountered before, constructed with lesser numbers coming to the left, and larger to the right hand side of each branch.
link: A. Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..72
A. Karttunen, Illustration of how binary trees (the second rightmost column) are encoded by A014486
xref: These are the mirror-images of binary trees given in A218610, i.e. a(n) = A057163(A218610(n)). A218613 gives the sizes of these trees. Cf. A218611.
